Done. `src/content/mrContext.js` now exports an async `getMRContext()` that returns all 5 required fields:

- **`projectId`** — from `window.gl.projectId` or `document.body.dataset.projectId`
- **`sourceBranch`** — from `gl.mrMetadata`, `gl.mr`, `<meta>` tags, or body data attrs
- **`mrIid`** — parsed from URL path
- **`mrPath`** — e.g. `/mygroup/myproject/-/merge_requests/42` (used as localStorage key suffix)
- **`sourceSha`** — from `gl.mrMetadata.headSha` or API fallback (may be null)

Returns `null` on non-MR pages. Falls back to `GET /api/v4/projects/:id/merge_requests/:iid` when the gl global is incomplete.

